This paper deals with the challenges of handling Big Data in the context of machine learning and classification. The paper focuses on the use of ensembles to improve classification performance, which is a common topic in the machine learning community (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of imbalanced data distribution, which is a common problem in classification tasks (cs.DS). The use of data preprocessing techniques to address this issue is also discussed, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a range of datasets, which is a common practice in computational engineering (cs.CE).
